🚀 5-Week UI/UX Plan for DeliverNow Food Delivery App
🗓 PHASE 1 — Weeks 1-3 → Mid-fidelity prototypes + testing
1️⃣ Empathize (Week 1)

✅ Goal: Understand real problems for the 4 personas

👉 Tasks:

Create 4 personas:

    Client / Customer

    Restaurant owner

    Runner / Delivery person

    Runner manager

Plan and conduct user research interviews / surveys (at least 5 people in total, ideally more)

    Example questions for each persona (I can help you write these)

    Choose a method: Google Forms, WhatsApp, phone, in-person

    Document pain points (e.g. wrong delivery times, too much cutlery, poor runner allocation)

💡 I can help:

    Draft user interview/survey questions

    Create persona templates

    Analyze raw responses to extract key pain points

2️⃣ Define (Week 1-2)

✅ Goal: Clearly state the problem to solve

👉 Tasks:

Write problem statements for each persona
(e.g. “Clients need accurate delivery estimates so they can plan their meals without frustration”)

    Map current user journeys (as-is) showing where problems occur

💡 I can help:

    Format your problem statements

    Draw the journey maps in tools like Figma, FigJam, Miro

3️⃣ Ideate (Week 2)

✅ Goal: Generate ideas and solutions

👉 Tasks:

Brainstorm solutions per persona (individually or as a team)

Sketch wireframes on paper or digitally

    Prioritize features (MoSCoW method: Must have / Should have / Could have / Won’t have)

💡 I can help:

    Facilitate idea prioritization

    Review your sketches, propose better UI patterns

4️⃣ Prototype (Week 2-3)

✅ Goal: Build mid-fidelity wireframes + link screens into journeys

👉 Tasks:

Design mid-fidelity prototypes (gray scale, no colors, focus on layout + flow)

    Mobile + Desktop for each persona

    Create clickable flows for one order journey

💡 I can help:

    Provide Figma file structures

    Suggest UI best practices

    Help you link screens into a flow

5️⃣ Test (Week 3)

✅ Goal: Validate mid-fidelity prototypes with users

👉 Tasks:

Test with at least 5 people

    Document feedback (what worked? what confused them?)

💡 I can help:

    Design test script

    Help you organize feedback in actionable points

🗓 PHASE 2 — Weeks 4-5 → High-fidelity prototypes + testing
6️⃣ Refine & Design Final UI (Week 4)

✅ Goal: Apply feedback + polish designs

👉 Tasks:

Adjust wireframes based on test results

Add color, fonts, iconography, imagery

    Ensure accessibility (contrast, font size)

💡 I can help:

    Create style guides (colors, typography)

    Suggest UI polish details

7️⃣ Final Testing (Week 5)

✅ Goal: Validate high-fidelity prototypes

👉 Tasks:

Test with at least 5 people again

    Document findings

💡 I can help:

    Prepare the presentation of user journeys + final prototypes

